2026-04-16 12:36:46 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['switched cables indicator LED (control module)'] hypothesis_explanation='There is a significant voltage drop between the relay output (p) and the load input cable (+) during the lamp-off interval, despite all measured wiring and connections testing nominal for continuity under static (unpowered) conditions. This suggests that the switched cables indicator LED in the control module is likely presenting a high resistance or intermittent open circuit only under actual load conditions. That would explain why both the main lamp and the indicator lamp in the load module simultaneously lose voltage, and why the relay itself appears fully functional. The voltage drop specifically across the switched cables indicator LED points to its internal intermittent (potentially heat-related) failure or a fractured solder joint, manifesting under operational current, but not seen under static continuity or low-current test conditions.'
